From: Huang Rui <vowstar@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: bump minimum required to 3.10 for cmake4 compat

CMake 4 drops support for cmake_minimum_required < 3.10 and emits a
QA warning today. Bump to 3.10 which is the next supported floor.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/975078
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -9,3 +9,3 @@
 # have available, but it's not guaranteed to work or be supported.
-cmake_minimum_required( VERSION 3.5 )
+cmake_minimum_required( VERSION 3.10 )

